history.content: I took EE20 with Babak and EE120 with Courtade, I would say that 120 is difficult in theory but also one of the more elegant classes. For Babak's class I spent maybe 4-5 hours per week on homeworks (in 20 he had a HW party every week which was extremely helpful, so since he's teaching it next semester that might be a big help!) for both classes and I'm by no means an amazing student. Personally I would think 106A/147would be hardest, but if you're on top of things I don't think it would be too bad.

children.subject: Hmmm I thought that 106a and 147 were considered pretty light courses.

history.content:
Hi,

I'm planning on taking EE120, EE106A, and EE147 along with an (easy) H/SS course. Does this course load seem doable? From what I've gathered only EE120 will be a best to deal with, and the other 2 EE classes should be relatively fine. In particular, how much time can I be expecting per week to spend on the assignments for these EE classes?

Thanks!
